  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims improving the outcome after brain resective surgery of epileptic patients by
      improving presurgical evaluations. In particular the specific goal is to evaluate the ability
      of non invasive neuroimaging (functional magnetic resonance imaging and
      electroencephalography) to provide presurgical maps of the functional areas of the brain and
      of the epileptogenic networks.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
